---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import ArtworkSchema from '../../../components/seo/ArtworkSchema.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Polvo eres';

const imgs = await Promise.all(
  Array.from({ length: 10 }, (_, i) =>
    import(`../../../assets/images/obras/polvo-eres/polvo-eres-${String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}.webp`)
  )
).then(m => m.map(x => x.default));
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Polvo eres — Work"
  description="Polvo eres (2024). Wall carving, brick wall, carving debris, plaster, paint. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>


  <ArtworkSchema
    title="Polvo eres"
    year="2024"
    medium="Wall carving"
    description="Inscription carved directly into the wall of the MAMU, Bogota. Biblical reference to dust and mortality."
    url="https://mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/polvo-eres/"
  />

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 012</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2024 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Wall carving, brick wall, carving debris, plaster, paint &nbsp;/&nbsp; Approx. 60 x 400 cm</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        {imgs.map((img, i) => (
          <img src={img.src} alt={`Polvo eres — Wall carving, MAMU ${i + 1}`} loading={i === 0 ? 'eager' : 'lazy'}>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Video -->
      <div class="work-page__video">
        <div class="work-page__video-header">
          <h3>VIDEO</h3>
          <span class="label">Polvo eres · 2:00 min</span>
        </div>
        <video controls preload="metadata" poster="">
          <source src="/maria-elvira-escallon/video/polvo-eres-obra.mp4" type="video/mp4">
          Your browser does not support HTML5 video.
        </video>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            The words are carved directly into a museum wall, exposing its internal
            layers — beneath the white paint, the brick layer is revealed — while
            debris accumulates at floor level. The inscription confronts us with the
            mortality of bodies, objects, and the architectures we inhabit.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The phrase "Polvo eres y en polvo te convertiras" [Thou art dust and unto
            dust thou shalt return] comes from Genesis (3:19) and responds to the Catholic
            ritual of Ash Wednesday. The artist explains that dust carries multiple meanings:
            humility (we are stardust), the transience of the body, and our nature as
            "conglomerates of vibrating particles."
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The work does not merely record deterioration; it transforms it into a
            sensitive reflection on the passage of time and the inescapable transience
            of life.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            <em>Polvo eres</em> is part of the "En la fabrica de polvo" [In the Dust
            Factory] axis of the anthological exhibition at MAMU. The title references
            the biblical phrase and connects to the central metaphor of the entire
            anthological exhibition — material transformation as a record of the passage
            of time, dust as the shared destiny of everything that exists.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Polvo eres</strong><br>
            2024<br><br>
            Wall carving, brick wall, carving debris, plaster, paint.<br><br>
            Approx. 60 x 400 cm<br>
            MAMU, Bogota
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Encuentros en la fabrica de polvo — MAMU, 2024
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2024). <em>Polvo eres</em>.
            Wall carving. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/polvo-eres/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    }
</style>
